*Problem:* Children from low-income "neighborhoods":http://babyutoledo.com/23/why-neighborhoods-matter enter Kindergarten 60 percent behind in learning development compared to their middle-class counterparts.

*Solution:* "Baby U":http://babyutoledo.com/10/how-baby-u-works gives "parents":http://babyutoledo.com/24/why-parents-matter the tools to reverse this education gap, so that every child in the "South Toledo Kids Zone":http://babyutoledo.com/19/south-toledo-kids-zone can start school ready to learn.

*Why?* We "believe":http://babyutoledo.com/22/why-baby-u that to change a neighborhood for the better, we must nurture it's greatest asset: *_The Family._* Baby U educates and strengthens our urban families. "Read more about us.":http://babyutoledo.com/3/about


